29
00:00:23.790 --> 00:00:25.959
♪

30
00:00:26.059 --> 00:00:28.661
We will make an alliance
with the Triarchy.

31
00:00:28.762 --> 00:00:30.362
I've had enough of
this cursed blockade.

32
00:00:30.430 --> 00:00:32.699
You cannot mean to treat
with the Free Cities.

33
00:00:32.799 --> 00:00:35.635
♪

34
00:00:35.735 --> 00:00:37.904
I thank Your Grace
for her blessings.

35
00:00:38.004 --> 00:00:40.173
♪

36
00:00:40.273 --> 00:00:42.709
All my life I have
endeavoured to serve.

37
00:00:42.809 --> 00:00:43.986
and somehow none of it matters.

38
00:00:44.010 --> 00:00:46.179
Sir Rickard. I wish to go out.

39
00:00:46.279 --> 00:00:50.650
♪

40
00:00:50.750 --> 00:00:53.686
There are older
things in this world

41
00:00:53.787 --> 00:00:56.689
than you. or I.
or living memory.

42
00:00:56.790 --> 00:00:59.659
You are not the player.
but a piece on the board.

43
00:00:59.759 --> 00:01:03.830
Do you accept me as
your queen and ruler?

44
00:01:03.930 --> 00:01:05.665
♪

45
00:01:05.765 --> 00:01:09.235
I wish you to go to Harrenhal.
Find out his intentions.

46
00:01:09.335 --> 00:01:11.704
whether he means to raise a
host for me or for himself.

47
00:01:11.805 --> 00:01:13.840
I have received rumour

48
00:01:13.940 --> 00:01:15.909
of the dragon
Seasmoke with a rider.

49
00:01:16.009 --> 00:01:17.710
The rider is your brother.

50
00:01:17.811 --> 00:01:21.081
If it is something
in the blood...

51
00:01:21.181 --> 00:01:25.118
I am of salt and sea. I
yearn for nothing else.

52
00:01:25.218 --> 00:01:26.586
You misled me. my lady.

53
00:01:26.686 --> 00:01:29.923
There is a large
dragon in the Vale.

54
00:01:30.023 --> 00:01:31.057
♪

55
00:01:31.157 --> 00:01:34.194
It is large. and formidable.

56
00:01:34.294 --> 00:01:37.097
But. alas. wild.

57
00:01:37.197 --> 00:01:39.232
The Riverlands are
held together by oaths.

58
00:01:39.332 --> 00:01:41.267
Then we shall go to
face your vassals

59
00:01:41.367 --> 00:01:43.203
and you will call
your lands to war.

60
00:01:43.303 --> 00:01:45.371
There is a problem.
They all hate you.

61
00:01:45.472 --> 00:01:48.241
The old ways call for
justice to be done.

62
00:01:48.341 --> 00:01:49.409
Seize him.

63
00:01:49.509 --> 00:01:52.112
He must now rectify
his grievous error.

64
00:01:52.212 --> 00:01:54.481
No. no. no!

65
00:01:54.581 --> 00:01:57.450
It crushes whoever wears it.

66
00:01:57.550 --> 00:02:00.320
I push him on your instruction.

67
00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:01.754
He is spent.

68
00:02:01.855 --> 00:02:04.958
It will be long before
he may rest again.

69
00:02:05.058 --> 00:02:07.927
They're looking for
Targaryen bastards.

70
00:02:08.027 --> 00:02:10.797
Each of you has
left behind a life

71
00:02:10.897 --> 00:02:13.900
to which you might never return.

72
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:18.238
If you survive. you
will be transformed.

73
00:02:18.338 --> 00:02:20.840
The dragon Vermithor.

74
00:02:20.940 --> 00:02:21.975
(Roaring and screams)

75
00:02:22.075 --> 00:02:24.777
And Silverwing.

76
00:02:24.878 --> 00:02:26.946
♪

77
00:02:27.046 --> 00:02:28.982
Who among you would be first?

78
00:02:29.082 --> 00:02:32.752
♪

79
00:02:32.852 --> 00:02:34.988
(Wild laughter)

80
00:02:35.088 --> 00:02:36.656
♪

81
00:02:36.756 --> 00:02:39.859
(Roaring)

82
00:02:39.959 --> 00:02:42.495
♪

83
00:02:42.595 --> 00:02:46.432
Let us raise an
army of bastards.

84
00:02:52.906 --> 00:02:56.042
(epic theme playing)

85
00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:04.074
Free Gift Cards and Tech Items with
Southwest Points: www.fairylandshop.me

86
00:03:41.154 --> 00:03:43.256
♪♪

87
00:04:36.809 --> 00:04:38.945
(theme concludes)

88
00:04:40.780 --> 00:04:43.916
(tense music playing)

89
00:04:48.788 --> 00:04:51.791
(indistinct chatter)

90
00:04:51.858 --> 00:04:54.060
Tyroshi captain:
These are our terms.

91
00:04:54.127 --> 00:04:57.730
One hundred of your
golden dragons.

92
00:04:57.797 --> 00:05:00.633
- Tyland Lannister: Per ship?
- (captain chuckles)

93
00:05:00.700 --> 00:05:01.868
captain: Per man.

94
00:05:01.934 --> 00:05:03.936
Tyland: I could not
produce such a coin.

95
00:05:04.003 --> 00:05:05.071
even if I wanted to.

96
00:05:05.138 --> 00:05:06.882
Myrish captain: Again.
you plead poverty.

97
00:05:06.906 --> 00:05:09.809
It is hollow stuff from
the mouth of a Lannister.

98
00:05:09.876 --> 00:05:11.377
Whose very stables
and sculleries

99
00:05:11.444 --> 00:05:13.379
are carved into a
mountain of gold.

100
00:05:13.446 --> 00:05:16.349
And we will need it
before this war is done.

101
00:05:16.416 --> 00:05:19.052
Break the blockade and
it will benefit you.

102
00:05:19.118 --> 00:05:21.020
Do you think that
we lack for buyers

103
00:05:21.087 --> 00:05:23.623
for our tapestries and perfumes?

104
00:05:23.690 --> 00:05:25.925
We sell where we please.

105
00:05:25.992 --> 00:05:27.360
blockade or no.

106
00:05:27.894 --> 00:05:30.596
Essos is as rich as it is vast.

107
00:05:30.663 --> 00:05:34.967
It seems you need us
more than we need you.

108
00:05:35.034 --> 00:05:37.970
- (sighs)
- (indistinct chatter)

109
00:05:38.905 --> 00:05:40.239
The Stepstones.

110
00:05:42.608 --> 00:05:44.510
(scoffs) What of them?

111
00:05:44.911 --> 00:05:46.646
Give us the Stepstones.

112
00:05:47.647 --> 00:05:49.415
A smattering of rocks...

113
00:05:50.116 --> 00:05:53.453
hardly a sacrifice to
the lords of Westeros.

114
00:05:53.519 --> 00:05:58.858
I... Those rocks have been
disputed for a generation.

115
00:06:00.059 --> 00:06:01.294
Your...

116
00:06:02.028 --> 00:06:06.065
pirates have waylaid ships.
taken slaves. cargo...

117
00:06:06.132 --> 00:06:08.901
Give them to us
outright. if you prevail.

118
00:06:08.968 --> 00:06:11.371
and all that will cease.

119
00:06:11.437 --> 00:06:13.106
We will impose a simple tax

120
00:06:13.172 --> 00:06:14.807
on those passing through.

121
00:06:14.874 --> 00:06:17.110
Recoup the losses
we took fighting

122
00:06:17.176 --> 00:06:18.821
- the Velaryon hordes.
- Tyland: Extortion.

123
00:06:18.845 --> 00:06:20.780
You will drive up the
price of basic goods.

124
00:06:20.847 --> 00:06:24.384
It is better than
starving. surely.

125
00:06:27.687 --> 00:06:30.757
Myrish captain: A fleet of warships.
then. sailing at your command.

126
00:06:30.823 --> 00:06:33.025
- They would break the blockade...
- Tyland: Hm.

127
00:06:33.092 --> 00:06:34.894
And hold the passage.

128
00:06:40.566 --> 00:06:41.868
Very well.

129
00:06:45.471 --> 00:06:48.307
The prince regent may
have me hanged for this.

130
00:06:48.374 --> 00:06:50.276
With the armada we send now.

131
00:06:50.343 --> 00:06:52.678
you can topple the prince regent

132
00:06:52.745 --> 00:06:55.081
and sit the Iron
Throne yourself.

133
00:06:59.051 --> 00:07:03.756
- (grunts) - Myrish captain: Of
course. there is one more condition.

134
00:07:03.823 --> 00:07:05.057
(sighs)

135
00:07:06.325 --> 00:07:07.493
Tyland: I was...

136
00:07:07.560 --> 00:07:10.029
rather set on a bath
and a flagon of wine.

137
00:07:10.096 --> 00:07:11.640
Myrish captain: The
commander of our fleet

138
00:07:11.664 --> 00:07:12.965
must agree to go with you.

139
00:07:13.032 --> 00:07:16.002
His name is Lohar. The sailors
are fiercely loyal to him.

140
00:07:16.068 --> 00:07:17.537
If. if he does not lead them.

141
00:07:17.603 --> 00:07:19.338
they will not fight.

142
00:07:21.774 --> 00:07:23.009
Very well.

143
00:07:23.576 --> 00:07:26.412
Let us meet this commander then.

144
00:07:27.313 --> 00:07:29.549
(clears throat. grunts)

145
00:07:29.615 --> 00:07:32.819
- (flies buzzing)
- (indistinct chatter)

146
00:07:37.423 --> 00:07:38.791
Admiral Lohar...

147
00:07:39.759 --> 00:07:42.028
this is Tyland Lannister.

148
00:07:42.094 --> 00:07:44.030
of Casterly Rock.

149
00:07:44.864 --> 00:07:47.433
Well met. Lord Tywin.

150
00:07:48.134 --> 00:07:49.435
Uh...

151
00:07:51.704 --> 00:07:53.806
it's Tyland.

152
00:07:55.441 --> 00:07:57.276
What sort of man are you?

153
00:07:58.544 --> 00:08:01.948
- I beg your pardon?
- A poet...

154
00:08:02.849 --> 00:08:04.116
a philosopher?

155
00:08:04.517 --> 00:08:07.386
I am the master of
ships at King's Landing.

156
00:08:07.787 --> 00:08:11.190
- You're thin.
- But also tall.

157
00:08:13.593 --> 00:08:17.129
I will not sail with a
man who cannot best me.

158
00:08:17.196 --> 00:08:19.432
(quiet laughter)

159
00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:21.634
(indistinct chatter)

160
00:08:22.902 --> 00:08:24.537
At. at what?

161
00:08:27.440 --> 00:08:30.443
(tense music playing)

162
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:33.646
(grumbles. roars)

163
00:08:45.491 --> 00:08:48.561
♪♪

164
00:08:54.734 --> 00:08:57.537
(people wailing. screaming)

165
00:09:07.079 --> 00:09:09.415
(music fades out)

166
00:09:10.283 --> 00:09:12.418
(Orwyle pouring tea)

167
00:09:13.819 --> 00:09:16.022
Some rum wouldn't go amiss.

168
00:09:17.156 --> 00:09:18.691
Your Grace.

169
00:09:19.358 --> 00:09:21.694
Just a little.

170
00:09:21.761 --> 00:09:24.096
(distant bell tolling)

171
00:09:29.535 --> 00:09:31.904
You're a good man. Orwyle.

172
00:09:36.008 --> 00:09:37.410
(door opens)

173
00:09:37.476 --> 00:09:39.579
(Aegon drinking)

174
00:09:42.448 --> 00:09:44.383
(birds chirping)

175
00:09:44.450 --> 00:09:45.785
A word. Your Grace?

176
00:09:46.919 --> 00:09:50.056
(exhales. clears throat)

177
00:10:04.003 --> 00:10:05.805
(door closes)

178
00:10:05.871 --> 00:10:08.975
I must ask you. Your
Grace. to steel yourself.

179
00:10:09.842 --> 00:10:11.978
We must leave King's
Landing. quickly.

180
00:10:12.044 --> 00:10:14.580
and we will not
return for some time.

181
00:10:16.148 --> 00:10:20.720
- What?
- The Pretender has found three new riders for her dragons.

182
00:10:20.786 --> 00:10:24.056
- That's impossible.
- Your brother thought the same.

183
00:10:24.123 --> 00:10:26.993
He flew to challenge
her and was rebuffed.

184
00:10:27.059 --> 00:10:29.295
Fled in terror.
from what I hear.

185
00:10:31.397 --> 00:10:33.132
He deserves no less.

186
00:10:33.332 --> 00:10:37.536
Be that as it may. he has
gone in fury to Sharp Point...

187
00:10:38.070 --> 00:10:40.940
and laid waste to the
whole of the town.

188
00:10:42.241 --> 00:10:44.777
Fucking mad cunt.

189
00:10:47.213 --> 00:10:48.814
She really did it then?

190
00:10:49.482 --> 00:10:51.150
I fear so.

191
00:10:52.551 --> 00:10:55.688
So. what was the fucking
point in all this then?

192
00:10:56.822 --> 00:10:59.058
The gods are cruel. Your Grace.

193
00:10:59.125 --> 00:11:02.528
but I hope you can
see the urgency.

194
00:11:02.595 --> 00:11:07.733
No. no. I am the
king. Why must I run?

195
00:11:08.100 --> 00:11:10.836
Because the prince regent
is going to kill you.

196
00:11:14.974 --> 00:11:16.118
You were in danger before.

197
00:11:16.142 --> 00:11:19.512
and now. he is thwarted
and he is angry.

198
00:11:19.578 --> 00:11:21.058
There is no telling
what he will do.

199
00:11:21.113 --> 00:11:22.581
but we have an opportunity

200
00:11:22.648 --> 00:11:25.918
- while he is away...
- An opportunity to push him out.

201
00:11:26.585 --> 00:11:28.487
Take me to my throne

202
00:11:28.554 --> 00:11:33.025
and once he returns. I shall
take him prisoner... hm?

203
00:11:33.092 --> 00:11:35.695
And what then?

204
00:11:35.761 --> 00:11:38.297
When Rhaenyra descends on
you with her seven dragons.

205
00:11:38.364 --> 00:11:40.833
and you. without
Vhagar. what then?

206
00:11:42.501 --> 00:11:43.569
W...

207
00:11:44.603 --> 00:11:45.738
Uh...

208
00:11:52.244 --> 00:11:53.713
I have. over the years.

209
00:11:53.779 --> 00:11:56.215
in anticipation of
little bumps in the road.

210
00:11:56.282 --> 00:11:58.984
moved the greater part of
Harrenhal's gold reserves

211
00:11:59.051 --> 00:12:01.120
to the Iron Bank in Braavos.

212
00:12:01.187 --> 00:12:03.622
We can live... well

213
00:12:03.689 --> 00:12:07.226
and remain until what
is coming has passed.

214
00:12:07.293 --> 00:12:09.328
(weak laughter)

215
00:12:09.862 --> 00:12:13.199
Y... You want to
take me to Essos

216
00:12:13.265 --> 00:12:15.401
to live with the goatfuckers.

217
00:12:16.435 --> 00:12:18.504
It's best to live. I think.

218
00:12:18.771 --> 00:12:21.207
- However you do it.
- Is it?

219
00:12:23.008 --> 00:12:25.578
My dragon is dead.

220
00:12:25.644 --> 00:12:27.580
I am burnt...

221
00:12:27.646 --> 00:12:31.450
and disgusting... and alone.

222
00:12:32.184 --> 00:12:33.753
And I'm a cripple.

223
00:12:37.356 --> 00:12:38.591
You are not alone.

224
00:12:38.657 --> 00:12:41.560
My cock is destroyed.
did they tell you that?

225
00:12:41.627 --> 00:12:45.564
Yeah. It burst into flames
like a sausage on the spit.

226
00:12:45.631 --> 00:12:47.099
Do not despair. Your Grace.

227
00:12:47.166 --> 00:12:49.168
There are better days ahead.

228
00:12:49.435 --> 00:12:51.904
Let your brother
and the Pretender

229
00:12:51.971 --> 00:12:55.040
destroy themselves in
blood and bitterness.

230
00:12:55.107 --> 00:12:56.442
When they are spent.

231
00:12:56.509 --> 00:12:58.010
and their armies in tatters.

232
00:12:58.077 --> 00:12:59.378
we will return.

233
00:12:59.445 --> 00:13:02.715
and the people will
rise up to meet us.

234
00:13:02.782 --> 00:13:05.818
I can't even piss without
it running down my leg.

235
00:13:05.885 --> 00:13:10.756
They will be tired of
endless deprivation and fear.

236
00:13:11.957 --> 00:13:15.261
They will hail the
returning king...

237
00:13:15.327 --> 00:13:18.264
his father's true heir.

238
00:13:19.565 --> 00:13:22.401
Aegon the Victorious...

239
00:13:22.468 --> 00:13:24.603
risen from the ashes.

240
00:13:25.538 --> 00:13:27.673
Aegon the Peacemaker.

241
00:13:30.609 --> 00:13:32.711
Aegon the Rebuilder.

242
00:13:36.115 --> 00:13:38.884
Aegon. the Realm's Delight.

243
00:13:40.686 --> 00:13:44.123
- (tense music playing)
- (wind blowing)

244
00:13:48.961 --> 00:13:51.063
(heavy breathing)

245
00:13:53.432 --> 00:13:55.534
(water flowing)

246
00:14:11.183 --> 00:14:12.251
(gasps)

247
00:14:23.963 --> 00:14:25.898
♪♪

248
00:14:26.432 --> 00:14:29.335
Ulf: This is more like
it. Hugh. don't you think?

249
00:14:29.401 --> 00:14:31.847
Hugh: We're meant to be at the
training yards learnin' the commands.

250
00:14:31.871 --> 00:14:33.339
Ulf: Yeah. and I will go.

251
00:14:33.405 --> 00:14:36.809
but surely they'd not deny
me my pleasure after so long.

252
00:14:36.876 --> 00:14:39.745
- I may never eat fish again.
- (music fades out)

253
00:14:40.479 --> 00:14:42.214
What are you doing here?

254
00:14:42.648 --> 00:14:44.116
Remove your feet from the table.

255
00:14:44.183 --> 00:14:45.951
- Ulf: I'd rather not.
- Hugh: Ulf.

256
00:14:46.018 --> 00:14:48.654
It's not up to you... Ulf.

257
00:14:48.721 --> 00:14:51.690
Who's it up to then... boy?

258
00:14:51.757 --> 00:14:55.160
He is the prince. Ulf.
Prince Jacaerys Velaryon.

259
00:14:55.995 --> 00:14:59.832
Prince Jacaerys Velaryon.
Right here. (chuckles)

260
00:14:59.899 --> 00:15:01.467
Who'd have thought it?

261
00:15:01.533 --> 00:15:02.635
He lives here.

262
00:15:03.269 --> 00:15:05.571
I'll have an apology from you.

263
00:15:05.638 --> 00:15:08.040
Ah! The young prince!

264
00:15:08.107 --> 00:15:10.075
And look at that hair.

265
00:15:11.744 --> 00:15:13.545
As dark as they say.

266
00:15:14.346 --> 00:15:16.882
Let them tell us we don't
have Targaryen blood. eh?

267
00:15:17.483 --> 00:15:21.287
- My mother is the queen and...
- Dragonriders both.

268
00:15:21.353 --> 00:15:24.556
You and I... cut
from the same cloth.

269
00:15:24.623 --> 00:15:28.460
It is a sacred inheritance
of which you know nothing.

270
00:15:28.527 --> 00:15:30.262
Forgive him. my prince.

271
00:15:30.329 --> 00:15:32.731
He is not much used to
the manners of court.

272
00:15:33.299 --> 00:15:34.934
Or any manners at all. I'd say.

273
00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:38.404
Do you know what has
happened this last hour. hm?

274
00:15:39.371 --> 00:15:40.940
The so-called prince regent

275
00:15:41.006 --> 00:15:42.875
has burned Sharp Point
down to its stones.

276
00:15:42.942 --> 00:15:45.044
Thousands of its
folk dead or lost.

277
00:15:45.110 --> 00:15:47.780
Its harbor in ashes.

278
00:15:47.846 --> 00:15:50.683
Will you prepare to
face such an enemy?

279
00:15:52.017 --> 00:15:54.887
Or will you stay here
and make yourself easy?

280
00:15:54.954 --> 00:15:57.156
If you hinder our efforts

281
00:15:57.222 --> 00:15:59.558
through sloth or unreadiness.

282
00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:00.793
I will see you hanged.

283
00:16:00.859 --> 00:16:03.462
and your body fed to
the dogs in the street.

284
00:16:04.196 --> 00:16:07.466
I-I meant no
disrespect. my prince.

285
00:16:22.147 --> 00:16:23.615
(indistinct chatter)

286
00:16:23.682 --> 00:16:26.085
Rhaenyra Targaryen: The new
riders are a boon to us.

287
00:16:26.151 --> 00:16:28.520
but now the deed is done.

288
00:16:28.587 --> 00:16:31.123
I cannot erase my doubts.

289
00:16:31.657 --> 00:16:33.225
We know little of who they are.

290
00:16:33.292 --> 00:16:36.128
and what is the strength
of their character.

291
00:16:36.195 --> 00:16:38.497
Addam of Hull. at
least. is known to you.

292
00:16:39.732 --> 00:16:41.800
He's a shipwright in my employ.

293
00:16:41.867 --> 00:16:45.504
and it is reported to me that
he is a man of integrity.

294
00:16:45.571 --> 00:16:50.042
I've had little to do
with him... to my regret.

295
00:16:50.676 --> 00:16:53.078
But the beasts
have been claimed.

296
00:16:53.145 --> 00:16:55.547
You now have a great advantage.

297
00:16:55.614 --> 00:16:57.616
You must strike. quickly.

298
00:16:57.683 --> 00:17:00.052
while the prince regent
mulls his next action.

299
00:17:01.420 --> 00:17:05.624
I had hoped my advantage
may be in deterrence.

300
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:07.459
Vhagar has ever been
our foremost threat.

301
00:17:07.526 --> 00:17:09.461
and she is now overmatched.

302
00:17:09.528 --> 00:17:11.130
Vhagar is not his only dragon.

303
00:17:11.196 --> 00:17:12.998
W... The third
brother is untested.

304
00:17:13.065 --> 00:17:14.400
has never left Oldtown.

305
00:17:14.466 --> 00:17:16.502
and his dragon is
younger than Vermax.

306
00:17:16.568 --> 00:17:18.203
But a dragon nonetheless.

307
00:17:18.270 --> 00:17:20.239
And you forget another.

308
00:17:21.874 --> 00:17:23.042
Helaena?

309
00:17:23.475 --> 00:17:25.911
She does not ride. She
has no taste for it.

310
00:17:25.978 --> 00:17:28.180
She may yet be compelled.

311
00:17:28.247 --> 00:17:30.049
- And her dragon...
- Dreamfyre.

312
00:17:30.115 --> 00:17:32.518
hatched when the
Conqueror was king.

313
00:17:33.519 --> 00:17:35.354
She is formidable.

314
00:17:35.421 --> 00:17:37.790
Still. Helaena is no warrior.

315
00:17:40.793 --> 00:17:43.162
Aemond thought
himself invincible.

316
00:17:43.228 --> 00:17:45.831
He has now discovered he is not.

317
00:17:45.898 --> 00:17:48.200
He'll be angry. desperate.

318
00:17:48.700 --> 00:17:50.936
He will not stop at
burning Sharp Point.

319
00:17:51.003 --> 00:17:53.372
and he will not be denied.

320
00:17:54.006 --> 00:17:55.441
You speak truly...

321
00:17:56.508 --> 00:17:58.210
though I wish it was not so.

322
00:17:58.277 --> 00:18:00.546
(soft chuckle)

323
00:18:00.612 --> 00:18:02.681
(indistinct chatter)

324
00:18:03.115 --> 00:18:04.650
How goes the Sea Snake?

325
00:18:06.185 --> 00:18:07.853
Better than new.

326
00:18:08.554 --> 00:18:10.589
We'll rejoin the
blockade on the morrow.

327
00:18:10.956 --> 00:18:14.560
Let our foes beware. be
they Lannister or Greyjoy.

328
00:18:15.861 --> 00:18:19.631
But... my ship is no
longer the Sea Snake.

329
00:18:19.998 --> 00:18:23.435
She was a testament
to my own glory.

330
00:18:23.502 --> 00:18:25.671
I've given her a new name.

331
00:18:27.873 --> 00:18:30.242
The Queen Who Never Was.

332
00:18:32.578 --> 00:18:33.946
Rhaenyra: Corlys...

333
00:18:35.013 --> 00:18:36.748
I thank you.

334
00:18:39.251 --> 00:18:40.786
(soft chuckle)

335
00:18:40.853 --> 00:18:44.590
What I do now... I do for her.

336
00:18:47.126 --> 00:18:49.094
Your Grace. you are ready.

337
00:18:49.161 --> 00:18:52.164
You have six dragons
under your banner.

338
00:18:52.698 --> 00:18:55.067
My ships sail at your command.

339
00:18:55.134 --> 00:18:56.668
and my men serve you.

340
00:18:57.236 --> 00:18:59.204
But the Lannisters are marching.

341
00:18:59.271 --> 00:19:01.874
and the Hightowers from Oldtown.

342
00:19:01.940 --> 00:19:06.111
You must crush this
beast at its head

343
00:19:06.178 --> 00:19:08.780
and before too many
days have flown.

344
00:19:11.950 --> 00:19:13.919
There is. of course...

345
00:19:13.986 --> 00:19:17.656
another player that
has yet to be revealed.

346
00:19:19.458 --> 00:19:21.393
Ah. Your Grace. a word.

347
00:19:21.460 --> 00:19:24.897
It seems the sheep on our
land has been sold upriver.

348
00:19:24.963 --> 00:19:27.766
My vassals have sent a
drove of swine instead.

349
00:19:27.833 --> 00:19:29.468
Dragons do eat pigs. I assume?

350
00:19:29.535 --> 00:19:31.870
Caraxes prefers them.
How goes your muster?

351
00:19:31.937 --> 00:19:33.448
We'll be ready to march
in two days' time.

352
00:19:33.472 --> 00:19:35.641
- See to those pigs.
- At once. Your Grace.

353
00:19:35.707 --> 00:19:39.545
Your Grace... Ser Alfred
Broome has come to see you.

354
00:19:39.611 --> 00:19:42.014
(laughs) Interesting.

355
00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:43.982
I am sent as an
emissary from the queen.

356
00:19:44.049 --> 00:19:46.518
to ascertain your movements
and your intentions.

357
00:19:46.585 --> 00:19:47.786
You've arrived just in time

358
00:19:47.853 --> 00:19:50.422
to see my new army. Broome.

359
00:19:50.489 --> 00:19:52.191
What do you think of it?

360
00:19:52.257 --> 00:19:53.959
It's very large.

361
00:19:54.026 --> 00:19:56.161
(Daemon chuckles softly)

362
00:19:56.228 --> 00:19:58.130
Lannister hesitates.

363
00:19:58.497 --> 00:20:01.333
I aim to march on King's
Landing before he can catch me.

364
00:20:01.400 --> 00:20:04.236
May I have a word in
private. Your Grace?

365
00:20:08.707 --> 00:20:10.709
I would speak honestly with you.

366
00:20:10.776 --> 00:20:12.253
Daemon Targaryen: I'd
expect nothing less.

367
00:20:12.277 --> 00:20:15.113
Alfred Broome: I was faithful
to the king. your brother.

368
00:20:15.180 --> 00:20:17.749
I pledged my banners
to Rhaenyra. his heir.

369
00:20:17.816 --> 00:20:19.651
I will never serve the usurpers

370
00:20:19.718 --> 00:20:21.520
or the whelps of Oldtown.

371
00:20:21.587 --> 00:20:23.488
but there are battles
to be fought...

372
00:20:23.555 --> 00:20:26.458
- voice (whispers): Traitor.
- And in times like this...

373
00:20:29.428 --> 00:20:31.196
Did you hear something?

374
00:20:32.898 --> 00:20:35.767
This place will have
you barking at the moon.

375
00:20:38.570 --> 00:20:40.339
While you have mustered an army.

376
00:20:40.405 --> 00:20:42.074
Rhaenyra has faltered...

377
00:20:42.140 --> 00:20:43.875
turning aside from our judgment.

378
00:20:43.942 --> 00:20:46.178
and taking a course. I
myself. deem reckless.

379
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:50.315
Rhaenyra will chart her own
course. for good or ill.

380
00:20:50.382 --> 00:20:52.484
But you are a leader of men.

381
00:20:53.685 --> 00:20:56.121
If you declare yourself.

382
00:20:56.188 --> 00:20:58.123
your lords will follow you.

383
00:20:58.557 --> 00:21:01.593
I never took you
for a turncloak...

384
00:21:02.461 --> 00:21:04.162
Ser Alfred.

385
00:21:06.865 --> 00:21:09.268
Rhaenyra's intentions are good.

386
00:21:10.869 --> 00:21:14.673
But what we need.
in this moment...

387
00:21:16.275 --> 00:21:17.776
is a king.

388
00:21:20.312 --> 00:21:23.749
(tense music playing)

389
00:21:23.815 --> 00:21:25.517
(chuckles)

390
00:21:36.228 --> 00:21:37.396
(sighs)

391
00:21:37.462 --> 00:21:39.531
♪♪

392
00:21:44.303 --> 00:21:46.114
Jasper "Ironrod" Wylde: It
appears that the Pretender

393
00:21:46.138 --> 00:21:47.978
sent boats to collect
those among the smallfolk

394
00:21:48.006 --> 00:21:50.642
who believed they had any
drop of Targaryen blood.

395
00:21:50.709 --> 00:21:52.611
Deception and subterfuge.

396
00:21:52.678 --> 00:21:55.714
Cowards. all of them. Put
an end to this madness.

397
00:21:55.781 --> 00:21:59.084
Let no vessel come or go from our
harbor without our inspection.

398
00:21:59.151 --> 00:22:01.420
This will hinder the work
of the fishing boats.

399
00:22:01.486 --> 00:22:03.622
The people depend on
them for sustenance.

400
00:22:03.689 --> 00:22:05.223
They will need no sustenance

401
00:22:05.290 --> 00:22:07.659
if they are slaughtered
by the enemy.

402
00:22:07.726 --> 00:22:10.128
We must all make our sacrifices.

403
00:22:12.431 --> 00:22:14.800
Helaena Targaryen: Why
does everybody hate us?

404
00:22:14.866 --> 00:22:16.802
Alicent Hightower:
They're unhappy...

405
00:22:16.868 --> 00:22:19.504
and unhappy people look
for someone to hate.

406
00:22:22.941 --> 00:22:24.843
We didn't order the blockade.

407
00:22:24.910 --> 00:22:28.246
No. but we are the crown. so
they expect us to break it.

408
00:22:29.514 --> 00:22:30.816
Drink this.

409
00:22:37.823 --> 00:22:40.659
I was happier
before I was queen.

410
00:22:46.998 --> 00:22:49.668
What would you think
about leaving this place?

411
00:22:52.304 --> 00:22:54.406
(birds cawing)

412
00:22:58.377 --> 00:23:00.379
Where would I go?

413
00:23:00.445 --> 00:23:02.547
(knocks on door)

414
00:23:06.618 --> 00:23:08.120
The prince regent. Your Grace.

415
00:23:08.186 --> 00:23:11.022
Helaena. Here you are. Mother.

416
00:23:13.458 --> 00:23:16.895
- I was just. just going to bed.
- The crown has need of your service.

417
00:23:16.962 --> 00:23:19.598
- Now?
- The Pretender has raised new riders against us.

418
00:23:19.664 --> 00:23:23.368
and we must answer in kind.

419
00:23:23.435 --> 00:23:25.270
I need you to fly with
Dreamfyre to battle.

420
00:23:25.337 --> 00:23:27.172
- Aemond.
- I do not wish to fight.

421
00:23:27.239 --> 00:23:29.408
Our wishes must take
second place now

422
00:23:29.474 --> 00:23:32.310
to what is necessary
to preserve the throne.

423
00:23:33.078 --> 00:23:35.213
I won't burn anyone.

424
00:23:37.182 --> 00:23:38.417
It isn't a question.

425
00:23:38.483 --> 00:23:40.228
- Aemond.
- They have defiled our birthright.

426
00:23:40.252 --> 00:23:41.896
- made commoners into dragonlords!
- Ow. ow!

427
00:23:41.920 --> 00:23:43.398
- Aemond! Aemond!
- It is a sin and must be punished!

428
00:23:43.422 --> 00:23:45.333
- May I remind you your sister is still the queen?
- Ow!

429
00:23:45.357 --> 00:23:47.192
As you were once!
And you see now

430
00:23:47.259 --> 00:23:48.860
what is the consequence
of your weakness!

431
00:23:48.927 --> 00:23:50.896
We are in peril today
more than yesterday!

432
00:23:50.962 --> 00:23:53.598
Was it peril that moved you to
burn the town of Sharp Point?

433
00:23:53.665 --> 00:23:56.435
Peril or basest fury at
your own humiliation?

434
00:23:56.501 --> 00:23:57.501
Ow!

435
00:23:58.103 --> 00:23:59.480
You wish to rule
the Seven Kingdoms.

436
00:23:59.504 --> 00:24:01.940
but you rain ruin and
death upon its smallfolk

437
00:24:02.007 --> 00:24:04.109
when you've been insulted

438
00:24:04.176 --> 00:24:06.044
because it makes you feel strong

439
00:24:06.111 --> 00:24:07.846
and now you seek to
corrupt your sister.

440
00:24:07.913 --> 00:24:10.182
of all our line. the
gentlest and most deserving

441
00:24:10.248 --> 00:24:11.793
- of your protection.
- And who will protect her

442
00:24:11.817 --> 00:24:12.994
if she cannot protect herself?

443
00:24:13.018 --> 00:24:14.462
And who will she be if
her mind is broken?!

444
00:24:14.486 --> 00:24:16.655
'Tis no longer our rule
that is threatened.

445
00:24:16.721 --> 00:24:17.756
our very lives.

446
00:24:17.823 --> 00:24:19.925
- Would you not have us prevail?
- Not like this.

447
00:24:23.495 --> 00:24:25.430
Not like this!

448
00:24:26.932 --> 00:24:30.302
(light. tense music playing)

449
00:24:42.147 --> 00:24:43.782
Grand Maester
Orwyle: Your Grace.

450
00:24:44.449 --> 00:24:45.784
Grand Maester.

451
00:24:46.985 --> 00:24:49.387
I must again request
your assistance.

452
00:24:50.055 --> 00:24:51.790
I need passage.

453
00:24:52.557 --> 00:24:54.559
And your discretion.

454
00:24:57.195 --> 00:25:00.565
(solemn music playing)

455
00:25:00.632 --> 00:25:03.835
- (quiet chatter)
- (ambient nature sounds)

456
00:25:06.204 --> 00:25:09.341
Gwayne Hightower: Do you
think nothing of your oath...

457
00:25:11.243 --> 00:25:12.744
Lord Commander?

458
00:25:14.746 --> 00:25:17.048
I think of nothing
else. my lord.

459
00:25:18.216 --> 00:25:20.485
Steward's son from Dorne

460
00:25:20.552 --> 00:25:23.388
fucking the queen of
the Seven Kingdoms.

461
00:25:25.323 --> 00:25:27.025
Former queen.

462
00:25:27.792 --> 00:25:29.761
She has broken no oath.
for all I may have done.

463
00:25:29.828 --> 00:25:32.631
- I could send you to the Wall.
- You could.

464
00:25:32.697 --> 00:25:35.734
Stain the Hightower
name for a generation.

465
00:25:36.101 --> 00:25:39.204
- King's mother and his Hand.
- She is my sister.

466
00:25:40.772 --> 00:25:41.940
(inhales)

467
00:25:42.007 --> 00:25:44.009
She saved my life.

468
00:25:44.910 --> 00:25:46.144
Twice.

469
00:25:46.211 --> 00:25:49.214
Once from the headsman's
axe and once from myself.

470
00:25:52.584 --> 00:25:55.453
Since then. she has been
the beacon I follow.

471
00:26:04.896 --> 00:26:08.767
Do not think I have
no shame in me. ser.

472
00:26:08.833 --> 00:26:11.703
Desire for women has brought
me grief after grief.

473
00:26:12.170 --> 00:26:15.607
- Gwayne: Then resist it.
- (Criston chuckles softly)

474
00:26:16.241 --> 00:26:17.909
Oh. would that it
were so simple.

475
00:26:17.976 --> 00:26:20.946
Your brothers in the
Kingsguard find a way.

476
00:26:24.049 --> 00:26:25.584
Do they?

477
00:26:27.152 --> 00:26:28.954
Mm. perhaps they do.

478
00:26:30.722 --> 00:26:33.325
Or perhaps all
men are corrupt...

479
00:26:34.960 --> 00:26:37.495
and true honor is a mist

480
00:26:38.263 --> 00:26:39.898
that melts in the morning.

481
00:26:42.367 --> 00:26:44.603
That is a bleak philosophy.

482
00:26:45.003 --> 00:26:46.972
I have no philosophy.

483
00:26:48.106 --> 00:26:50.508
Or rather. my
philosophy was this.

484
00:26:52.777 --> 00:26:54.012
To protect the righteous

485
00:26:54.079 --> 00:26:56.681
and dispense
justice on the rest.

486
00:26:58.750 --> 00:27:00.018
But now...

487
00:27:03.254 --> 00:27:05.190
You saw what I saw.

488
00:27:10.195 --> 00:27:14.499
The dragons dance. and men are
like dust under their feet.

489
00:27:17.869 --> 00:27:21.506
And all our fine thoughts.
all our... endeavors

490
00:27:21.573 --> 00:27:23.308
are as nothing.

491
00:27:28.980 --> 00:27:32.017
We march now toward
our annihilation.

492
00:27:38.289 --> 00:27:41.026
To die will be a kind of relief.

493
00:27:45.497 --> 00:27:47.065
Don't you think?

494
00:27:54.272 --> 00:27:57.409
(unsettling music playing)

495
00:28:21.066 --> 00:28:22.801
- (Sharako yells)
- (crowd cheering)

496
00:28:22.867 --> 00:28:25.003
(heavy breathing. grunts)

497
00:28:25.070 --> 00:28:27.572
- (crowd shouting)
- (Sharako laughing)

498
00:28:31.376 --> 00:28:33.678
(crowd shouting. laughing)

499
00:28:33.978 --> 00:28:36.448
(Tyland yells. pants)

500
00:28:38.149 --> 00:28:40.285
(Tyland grunting)

501
00:28:42.120 --> 00:28:43.455
(Sharako laughs)

502
00:28:45.190 --> 00:28:47.292
(yells. grunts)

503
00:28:48.893 --> 00:28:51.029
(heavy breathing)

504
00:28:54.399 --> 00:28:56.101
(groaning)

505
00:29:00.739 --> 00:29:01.973
(laughs)

506
00:29:02.307 --> 00:29:04.709
(crowd chanting "Lohar")

507
00:29:04.776 --> 00:29:06.211
(grunting)

508
00:29:08.012 --> 00:29:09.247
(crowd quiets)

509
00:29:09.314 --> 00:29:10.982
- (grunts)
- (Sharako yelps)

510
00:29:13.084 --> 00:29:15.220
(heavy breathing)

511
00:29:15.987 --> 00:29:18.089
(all silent)

512
00:29:20.024 --> 00:29:21.024
(spits)

513
00:29:26.464 --> 00:29:28.733
You have impressed
me. Lord Tyman.

514
00:29:29.634 --> 00:29:33.271
King's Landing has sent a
most doughty ambassador.

515
00:29:33.338 --> 00:29:35.039
(panting)

516
00:29:36.207 --> 00:29:42.013
I hope... you will testify to
the worth of the ambassador...

517
00:29:42.080 --> 00:29:45.817
by agreeing to his most
(pants) humble request.

518
00:29:45.884 --> 00:29:49.087
I will most certainly
consider it.

519
00:29:49.788 --> 00:29:50.788
(spits)

520
00:29:56.394 --> 00:29:58.263
After dinner.

521
00:30:02.433 --> 00:30:05.136
Have you ever eaten the
flesh of your enemies?

522
00:30:05.203 --> 00:30:06.971
(panting) What?

523
00:30:09.140 --> 00:30:12.277
I have not and I would not.

524
00:30:13.711 --> 00:30:18.383
So you reject the
hospitality of my house.

525
00:30:26.224 --> 00:30:29.060
- (laughs)
- (crowd laughs)

526
00:30:29.127 --> 00:30:30.628
A jest. my lord.

527
00:30:31.763 --> 00:30:34.799
(laughing) What do
you take me for?

528
00:30:37.769 --> 00:30:39.037
A jest!

529
00:30:40.038 --> 00:30:41.339
Come.

530
00:30:44.475 --> 00:30:47.512
- (grunts)
- (crowd yells. laughs)

531
00:30:52.083 --> 00:30:54.419
(nearby dragon grumbles)

532
00:30:55.987 --> 00:30:58.590
It does not befit
a prince to pout.

533
00:31:00.291 --> 00:31:01.826
I'm not pouting.

534
00:31:01.893 --> 00:31:03.428
What would you call it. then?

535
00:31:05.730 --> 00:31:09.167
- I'm reading.
- While your mother waits?

536
00:31:12.937 --> 00:31:14.672
You're angry.

537
00:31:17.775 --> 00:31:18.843
Aren't you?

538
00:31:18.910 --> 00:31:20.578
I don't see what
good it would do.

539
00:31:21.746 --> 00:31:24.082
They are an insult to us.

540
00:31:24.148 --> 00:31:26.017
To what makes us Targaryens.

541
00:31:26.084 --> 00:31:27.886
If any common lout
can ride a dragon.

542
00:31:27.952 --> 00:31:31.022
- then...
- That does not make me common. Or you.

543
00:31:32.257 --> 00:31:34.893
- You know what I am.
- I don't care.

544
00:31:34.959 --> 00:31:37.028
You are the crown prince.

545
00:31:37.095 --> 00:31:38.830
the son of the rightful queen.

546
00:31:38.897 --> 00:31:40.265
and here you are sulking

547
00:31:40.331 --> 00:31:41.876
because you believe that
if not for the dragon

548
00:31:41.900 --> 00:31:43.534
or the trappings
of your station.

549
00:31:43.601 --> 00:31:45.236
that you are nothing.

550
00:31:45.303 --> 00:31:47.939
(chuckles) Do you believe that
you are the first noble heir

551
00:31:48.006 --> 00:31:50.441
who was not sired
by his noble father?

552
00:31:50.942 --> 00:31:53.278
Such is the way of
the world. Jace.

553
00:31:53.344 --> 00:31:56.514
and in resenting it. you
only diminish yourself.

554
00:31:56.581 --> 00:31:58.182
Easy enough to say.

555
00:31:58.583 --> 00:32:01.119
I've heard the whispers
the whole of my life.

556
00:32:01.185 --> 00:32:03.421
Then prove to them
that you are worthy.

557
00:32:03.488 --> 00:32:05.056
Get up and take your place

558
00:32:05.123 --> 00:32:06.624
by your mother's side.

559
00:32:08.693 --> 00:32:12.063
(light. tense music playing)

560
00:32:17.302 --> 00:32:19.404
(wind blowing)

561
00:32:21.306 --> 00:32:23.007
(shivering)

562
00:32:24.809 --> 00:32:26.911
♪♪

563
00:32:30.949 --> 00:32:34.118
Tyland (singing halfheartedly): ♪
Here come my lads. my comely boys ♪

564
00:32:34.185 --> 00:32:36.621
♪ And split your sacks ashore ♪

565
00:32:36.688 --> 00:32:39.891
♪ For you'll be
sail-sailing many days ♪

566
00:32:39.958 --> 00:32:41.659
♪ Afore you get some more ♪

567
00:32:42.226 --> 00:32:45.096
♪ So grease the mast
and send it up ♪

568
00:32:46.197 --> 00:32:48.533
♪ Betwixt the wind and water ♪

569
00:32:49.100 --> 00:32:51.469
♪ Hoist. me lads.
and hoist again ♪

570
00:32:52.036 --> 00:32:55.473
♪ Salute the
captain's daughter ♪

571
00:32:59.644 --> 00:33:01.813
Well done. Lord Tyrod!

572
00:33:10.355 --> 00:33:13.825
Good song. well delivered.

573
00:33:13.891 --> 00:33:16.260
(indistinct chatter)

574
00:33:16.327 --> 00:33:18.629
(futilely) It's Tyland.

575
00:33:20.031 --> 00:33:22.934
You have proven yourself
most accommodating.

576
00:33:23.001 --> 00:33:26.371
And more accomplished than one
would think. to look at you.

577
00:33:26.437 --> 00:33:29.540
Hm. Well... Hm.

578
00:33:31.642 --> 00:33:35.079
I will be pleased to
sail at your side.

579
00:33:36.814 --> 00:33:39.417
- Oh.
- And my captains with me.

580
00:33:45.056 --> 00:33:46.991
(chattering stops)

581
00:33:47.058 --> 00:33:49.927
To the Gullet on the morrow!

582
00:33:49.994 --> 00:33:52.096
(all cheering)

583
00:33:56.367 --> 00:33:58.503
And let the Sea Snake

584
00:33:58.569 --> 00:34:01.072
rue the day we meet again.

585
00:34:01.139 --> 00:34:03.541
(all cheering)

586
00:34:05.410 --> 00:34:07.779
Ya! My king will
be well pleased.

587
00:34:07.845 --> 00:34:09.380
To friendship!

588
00:34:09.447 --> 00:34:11.182
(cheering)

589
00:34:12.717 --> 00:34:15.720
(percussive music playing)

590
00:34:15.787 --> 00:34:17.755
(indistinct chatter)

591
00:34:23.895 --> 00:34:25.897
It is late.

592
00:34:25.963 --> 00:34:27.932
(Tyland clears throat)

593
00:34:28.533 --> 00:34:29.734
Oh!

594
00:34:30.034 --> 00:34:31.769
Before you go...

595
00:34:32.403 --> 00:34:33.604
Lord Tyland.

596
00:34:33.671 --> 00:34:34.739
Mm.

597
00:34:36.140 --> 00:34:37.642
You are a handsome man.

598
00:34:37.708 --> 00:34:43.581
and you have proven
your worth and virility.

599
00:34:45.583 --> 00:34:47.752
I wish to have children by you.

600
00:34:51.956 --> 00:34:55.693
(stammers) You. you...
You want me to...

601
00:34:55.760 --> 00:34:57.061
Indeed.

602
00:34:59.530 --> 00:35:01.799
I want you to fuck my wives.

603
00:35:06.304 --> 00:35:09.674
How many wives do you have?

604
00:35:13.244 --> 00:35:16.013
Ulf: (gulps) More wine here!

605
00:35:17.582 --> 00:35:19.784
Taming a dragon is thirsty work.

606
00:35:24.589 --> 00:35:27.425
Oh. and some more of
these little birds.

607
00:35:28.392 --> 00:35:29.861
(sighs)

608
00:35:34.232 --> 00:35:35.800
Rhaenyra: A toast.

609
00:35:37.435 --> 00:35:39.770
To our new riders.

610
00:35:40.771 --> 00:35:43.007
The three of you are
not of noble birth.

611
00:35:43.074 --> 00:35:46.110
but you have done a thing
never dreamed of before now.

612
00:35:46.177 --> 00:35:49.013
- (Ulf chuckling)
- (Jacaerys sighs)

613
00:35:57.855 --> 00:36:01.259
I have entrusted you with a
power only few have known.

614
00:36:01.325 --> 00:36:05.062
And I charge you to take it
up with fealty and respect.

615
00:36:05.730 --> 00:36:09.800
Serve me well. and I will
make you knights of the realm.

616
00:36:09.867 --> 00:36:12.670
Huh? What do you
think of that. boys?

617
00:36:13.137 --> 00:36:15.773
We'll be knights...
just like that.

618
00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:18.042
We will not fail you. my queen.

619
00:36:19.777 --> 00:36:21.512
What must we do?

620
00:36:23.748 --> 00:36:27.084
I had thought the mere fact of
you might stay the enemy's hand.

621
00:36:28.853 --> 00:36:30.621
But Lord Corlys is right.

622
00:36:30.955 --> 00:36:34.892
We must strike while we
have the advantage...

623
00:36:34.959 --> 00:36:36.160
and end this war.

624
00:36:36.494 --> 00:36:39.230
Learn your beasts
and your commands.

625
00:36:39.630 --> 00:36:41.332
You will fly in two days' time.

626
00:36:42.033 --> 00:36:45.703
The strongholds of the usurper.
Oldtown and Lannisport.

627
00:36:45.770 --> 00:36:49.440
and their armies.
all must be subdued.

628
00:36:50.074 --> 00:36:53.044
Alone. without allies. he will
have no choice but to surrender.

629
00:36:53.110 --> 00:36:55.413
You wish for us
to kill innocents.

630
00:36:55.479 --> 00:36:57.748
- And so many.
- Jacaerys Velaryon: It is hard...

631
00:36:58.649 --> 00:37:00.518
but it cannot be helped.

632
00:37:00.585 --> 00:37:01.719
(Ulf grunts)

633
00:37:05.289 --> 00:37:07.592
We must break the
will of our enemy...

634
00:37:08.426 --> 00:37:09.727
or more will die in a struggle

635
00:37:09.794 --> 00:37:11.295
that stretches on without end.

636
00:37:11.362 --> 00:37:13.898
What about Vhagar?

637
00:37:13.965 --> 00:37:19.870
She is fearsome...
but she is one dragon.

638
00:37:19.937 --> 00:37:21.949
The prince regent cannot
defend against all of us.

639
00:37:21.973 --> 00:37:25.710
I'll take him on myself.
Silverwing's a goer. she is.

640
00:37:25.776 --> 00:37:28.112
- We're afraid of nothing.
- Addam of Hull: Hm.

641
00:37:28.512 --> 00:37:30.948
- Even if you are.
- There will be time enough

642
00:37:31.015 --> 00:37:32.817
to see which one
of us is a coward.

643
00:37:33.918 --> 00:37:36.454
I said more of
these little birds!

644
00:37:37.922 --> 00:37:42.360
A knight will comport himself
with grace at the queen's table.

645
00:37:42.693 --> 00:37:44.161
Best make me a knight. then.

646
00:37:48.366 --> 00:37:50.334
You forget yourself...

647
00:37:51.902 --> 00:37:53.170
friend.

648
00:37:55.172 --> 00:37:56.607
(scoffs)

649
00:37:57.375 --> 00:37:59.610
A sense of humor
would do you all good.

650
00:38:04.315 --> 00:38:06.083
(footsteps approach)

651
00:38:10.488 --> 00:38:13.858
(whispers) There is a message
from Harrenhal. Your Grace.

652
00:38:20.264 --> 00:38:21.332
Daemon?

653
00:38:21.399 --> 00:38:24.602
The castellan. Ser Simon Strong.

654
00:38:24.669 --> 00:38:27.371
Daemon has raised his army...

655
00:38:27.438 --> 00:38:30.641
- but Ser Simon fears treachery.
- (sighs)

656
00:38:33.811 --> 00:38:35.780
I will not allow it.

657
00:38:37.815 --> 00:38:38.883
Addam...

658
00:38:40.017 --> 00:38:41.319
come with me.

659
00:38:47.024 --> 00:38:48.326
Ulf: Thank you.

660
00:38:49.593 --> 00:38:50.661
Birds.

661
00:38:55.299 --> 00:38:57.401
(water dripping)

662
00:39:12.183 --> 00:39:14.385
Do you never sleep. witch?

663
00:39:19.190 --> 00:39:21.425
I'm goin' to the godswood.

664
00:39:31.235 --> 00:39:33.337
(wind blowing)

665
00:39:47.551 --> 00:39:51.655
(antlered human shape
clip-clopping. grumbles)

666
00:39:51.722 --> 00:39:54.859
(eerie music playing)

667
00:39:58.963 --> 00:40:02.199
When you came here.
you were a closed fist.

668
00:40:04.502 --> 00:40:08.372
You wished to bend the
world to your will.

669
00:40:10.775 --> 00:40:13.444
But you've discovered.
I think. that...

670
00:40:13.511 --> 00:40:16.313
this world will not be governed.

671
00:40:22.620 --> 00:40:26.257
There are omens here
for those who seek them.

672
00:40:29.593 --> 00:40:31.195
You do not scoff?

673
00:40:31.262 --> 00:40:34.899
- I'm no longer inclined to.
- (Alys chuckles)

674
00:40:36.000 --> 00:40:38.035
I'm pleased to hear it.

675
00:40:38.102 --> 00:40:40.171
♪♪

676
00:40:49.580 --> 00:40:53.317
Do you wish. then. to
learn what is given to you?

677
00:41:01.425 --> 00:41:03.561
All your life. you
have sought to command

678
00:41:03.627 --> 00:41:05.329
your own fate.

679
00:41:07.531 --> 00:41:09.733
(grabs Daemon's hand)

680
00:41:09.800 --> 00:41:12.036
But today you are ready.

681
00:41:12.102 --> 00:41:14.171
♪♪

682
00:41:29.320 --> 00:41:31.288
♪♪

683
00:41:31.355 --> 00:41:33.624
(bark crackling)

684
00:41:35.860 --> 00:41:37.862
(music intensifies)

685
00:41:37.928 --> 00:41:39.997
(crackling)

686
00:41:43.868 --> 00:41:45.870
(raven cawing)

687
00:41:45.936 --> 00:41:48.138
♪♪

688
00:41:49.473 --> 00:41:51.575
(soldiers fighting)

689
00:42:01.552 --> 00:42:03.087
(explosion booms)

690
00:42:03.854 --> 00:42:06.924
(light music playing)

691
00:42:06.991 --> 00:42:09.360
(dragon calls. screeches)

692
00:42:13.831 --> 00:42:15.900
♪♪

693
00:42:29.580 --> 00:42:32.716
(powerful music playing)

694
00:42:35.419 --> 00:42:38.622
Helaena (echoes):
It's all a story...

695
00:42:46.697 --> 00:42:49.533
and you are but one part in it.

696
00:42:51.302 --> 00:42:53.437
You know your part.

697
00:42:53.504 --> 00:42:56.540
- (music fades out)
- (wind blowing)

698
00:42:56.607 --> 00:42:58.709
(bark crackling)

699
00:43:03.547 --> 00:43:06.083
You know what you must do.

700
00:43:06.483 --> 00:43:08.252
(footsteps approach)

701
00:43:14.692 --> 00:43:16.493
Sister.

702
00:43:16.560 --> 00:43:18.529
We share the same blood.

703
00:43:18.596 --> 00:43:20.564
you and I.

704
00:43:20.631 --> 00:43:23.667
I know you wish
no harm to anyone.

705
00:43:25.836 --> 00:43:28.038
But in a time like this.

706
00:43:28.105 --> 00:43:30.975
when the good of the
realm depends on us...

707
00:43:33.877 --> 00:43:36.880
Our mother is not a dragonrider.

708
00:43:37.281 --> 00:43:39.116
She cannot understand

709
00:43:39.183 --> 00:43:42.419
that you and I have
a truer call to heed.

710
00:43:47.057 --> 00:43:48.792
Come with me...

711
00:43:49.893 --> 00:43:51.428
to Harrenhal?

712
00:43:53.230 --> 00:43:56.333
We will lay waste to
Daemon and his army.

713
00:43:57.001 --> 00:44:02.272
Let our enemy see that we will
answer outrage with outrage.

714
00:44:02.339 --> 00:44:04.441
And if I refuse?

715
00:44:07.177 --> 00:44:10.014
Will you burn me
as you did Aegon?

716
00:44:13.917 --> 00:44:16.687
- That is a lie.
- I saw it.

717
00:44:20.190 --> 00:44:24.194
You burned him and
you let him fall.

718
00:44:28.065 --> 00:44:30.200
What you say is treason.

719
00:44:32.469 --> 00:44:35.039
Aegon will be king again.

720
00:44:38.008 --> 00:44:40.544
He's yet to see victory.

721
00:44:41.478 --> 00:44:44.248
He sits on a wooden throne.

722
00:44:44.915 --> 00:44:46.417
And you...

723
00:44:50.788 --> 00:44:52.923
(whispers) you'll be dead.

724
00:44:55.426 --> 00:44:58.262
You were swallowed
up in the God's Eye.

725
00:44:58.328 --> 00:45:00.330
and you were never seen again.

726
00:45:02.366 --> 00:45:05.536
(light. tense music playing)

727
00:45:05.602 --> 00:45:08.338
(whispers) I could
have you killed.

728
00:45:09.073 --> 00:45:11.909
(softly) It wouldn't
change anything.

729
00:45:12.976 --> 00:45:15.045
♪♪

730
00:45:23.721 --> 00:45:27.157
- (intense music playing)
- (Syrax roars)

731
00:45:27.491 --> 00:45:29.593
(Seasmoke roars)

732
00:45:32.563 --> 00:45:34.698
(Caraxes grumbles)

733
00:45:37.735 --> 00:45:39.236
(roars)

734
00:45:49.046 --> 00:45:51.615
♪♪

735
00:45:51.682 --> 00:45:53.784
(all yelling)

736
00:45:57.321 --> 00:45:59.890
(singers vocalizing)

737
00:46:02.392 --> 00:46:04.495
(dragons calling)

738
00:46:14.204 --> 00:46:15.939
(screeches)

739
00:46:22.012 --> 00:46:23.514
(roars)

740
00:46:26.784 --> 00:46:28.852
♪♪

741
00:46:32.289 --> 00:46:35.425
I am the castellan. Ser
Simon Strong. Your Grace.

742
00:46:35.492 --> 00:46:37.528
Well met.

743
00:46:37.594 --> 00:46:39.530
Welcome to Harrenhal. my queen.

744
00:46:39.596 --> 00:46:41.165
I did not think to
see you here yourself.

745
00:46:41.231 --> 00:46:44.268
(exhales) Your message
gave me much concern.

746
00:46:44.334 --> 00:46:47.004
Yes. I must admit I
had reason to fear.

747
00:46:48.939 --> 00:46:50.774
But come. see for yourself.

748
00:46:55.012 --> 00:46:57.114
(Seasmoke calls)

749
00:47:01.151 --> 00:47:03.287
(indistinct chatter)

750
00:47:19.570 --> 00:47:21.572
(chatter quiets)

751
00:47:21.638 --> 00:47:24.007
(Syrax screeching)

752
00:47:25.676 --> 00:47:27.177
(roars)

753
00:47:32.416 --> 00:47:33.951
(silence)

754
00:47:34.017 --> 00:47:37.054
(light. tense music playing)

755
00:48:06.583 --> 00:48:08.685
♪♪

756
00:48:20.898 --> 00:48:23.433
I wasn't expecting you.

757
00:48:25.702 --> 00:48:28.138
That seems rather a
lapse in foresight.

758
00:48:31.141 --> 00:48:34.378
- I see you have done well here.
- They are sworn to me.

759
00:48:34.978 --> 00:48:37.281
And not a moment too soon.

760
00:48:41.985 --> 00:48:44.421
And to whom are you sworn?

761
00:49:00.437 --> 00:49:02.572
(speaking High Valyrian)

762
00:49:19.456 --> 00:49:22.292
(speaking High Valyrian)

763
00:49:41.878 --> 00:49:43.981
The realm's only hope...

764
00:49:44.514 --> 00:49:46.116
is a leader who can unite it

765
00:49:46.183 --> 00:49:49.786
and my brother chose... you.

766
00:49:52.756 --> 00:49:55.892
(light music playing)

767
00:50:08.772 --> 00:50:11.208
You are the true
queen. Rhaenyra.

768
00:50:12.109 --> 00:50:14.011
First of Her Name.

769
00:50:14.411 --> 00:50:16.446
Protector of the Realm.

770
00:50:16.980 --> 00:50:21.018
I am meant to serve you.
and all of these with me.

771
00:50:21.084 --> 00:50:22.953
until death

772
00:50:23.020 --> 00:50:25.555
or the end of our story.

773
00:50:29.893 --> 00:50:32.996
(music intensifies)

774
00:50:51.281 --> 00:50:53.417
(music softens)

775
00:50:57.921 --> 00:51:00.057
(speaking High Valyrian)

776
00:51:07.898 --> 00:51:10.033
(speaking High Valyrian)

777
00:51:15.105 --> 00:51:16.807
My queen.

778
00:51:26.583 --> 00:51:30.020
(shouting) For every
one of us who falls...

779
00:51:30.087 --> 00:51:32.289
a hundred of them!

780
00:51:32.355 --> 00:51:35.492
There will be no mercy!

781
00:51:35.826 --> 00:51:38.161
We fight for our queen!

782
00:51:38.462 --> 00:51:40.063
(all cheering)

783
00:51:40.130 --> 00:51:43.266
(heroic music playing)

784
00:51:47.270 --> 00:51:49.406
(Daemon shouting)

785
00:51:51.308 --> 00:51:53.410
♪♪

786
00:52:03.687 --> 00:52:06.022
(music softens)

787
00:52:06.089 --> 00:52:07.791
(cranking)

788
00:52:09.025 --> 00:52:11.161
(indistinct chatter)

789
00:52:18.735 --> 00:52:20.837
(seagulls cawing)

790
00:52:23.440 --> 00:52:25.809
You sent for me. Lord Hand.

791
00:52:27.477 --> 00:52:30.447
Gulls are flying low today.

792
00:52:30.514 --> 00:52:32.382
The weather will change.

793
00:52:32.983 --> 00:52:35.418
Not until late. I think. but...

794
00:52:35.485 --> 00:52:37.888
- I will ready the storm sails.
- We join the blockade.

795
00:52:37.954 --> 00:52:42.392
and are like to find ourselves
in peril. sooner than late.

796
00:52:43.293 --> 00:52:46.930
I wish to set out on good
terms with my first mate.

797
00:52:47.430 --> 00:52:49.132
Have I been remiss in my duties?

798
00:52:49.199 --> 00:52:52.636
You've done what is
asked of you. and more.

799
00:52:52.702 --> 00:52:56.306
But you are curt... silent.

800
00:52:56.373 --> 00:52:59.476
and the men find you distant.

801
00:53:00.043 --> 00:53:02.612
You cannot lead if
you do not inspire.

802
00:53:02.979 --> 00:53:05.882
Well. I never asked to
lead. as you well know.

803
00:53:08.385 --> 00:53:11.755
You have been given a position to
which all who serve here aspire.

804
00:53:14.191 --> 00:53:16.159
Forgive me. my lord.

805
00:53:16.226 --> 00:53:18.595
I will endeavor
to improve myself.

806
00:53:19.329 --> 00:53:21.431
(birds cawing)

807
00:53:22.566 --> 00:53:25.168
(softly) I am
trying to help you.

808
00:53:31.575 --> 00:53:33.176
You want to help me?

809
00:53:34.844 --> 00:53:37.147
Is this the help you offer
after all these years?

810
00:53:37.214 --> 00:53:39.616
A reminder to be grateful?

811
00:53:40.350 --> 00:53:41.851
I mean no offense.

812
00:53:42.586 --> 00:53:43.920
You may go.

813
00:53:47.357 --> 00:53:49.759
Do you know what
it was like for us?

814
00:53:50.927 --> 00:53:53.063
To grow up fatherless...

815
00:53:53.129 --> 00:53:55.065
to be sneered upon as bastards.

816
00:53:55.131 --> 00:53:56.900
never sure of the
bread to feed us?

817
00:53:56.967 --> 00:53:59.603
D-D-Do you know what
hunger does to a boy?

818
00:54:00.537 --> 00:54:02.239
What grief does?

819
00:54:02.806 --> 00:54:05.342
- Or shame?
- You are dismissed.

820
00:54:05.675 --> 00:54:07.777
I sold fish in the market

821
00:54:07.844 --> 00:54:10.547
from cold dawn until sunset.

822
00:54:10.614 --> 00:54:13.049
putting by coppers to
stave off the winter.

823
00:54:13.116 --> 00:54:16.219
and I watched the man
who sired me walk past

824
00:54:16.286 --> 00:54:19.055
with his son and heir

825
00:54:19.122 --> 00:54:22.092
with a fur around
his shoulders...

826
00:54:22.559 --> 00:54:27.831
choosing sweetmeats to eat
after supper by the fire.

827
00:54:29.833 --> 00:54:32.068
And now that boy is dead.

828
00:54:32.135 --> 00:54:34.070
And his sister before him.

829
00:54:34.137 --> 00:54:35.739
And the heir that
took his place.

830
00:54:35.805 --> 00:54:39.643
And now. now. now
you remember I live.

831
00:54:41.044 --> 00:54:42.946
Now you wish to...

832
00:54:43.013 --> 00:54:45.849
suddenly to scatter the
crumbs of your favor.

833
00:54:48.084 --> 00:54:52.355
I am an honorable man. and I
will serve you because I must.

834
00:54:52.856 --> 00:54:55.759
But if it is all the same.

835
00:54:55.825 --> 00:55:00.430
I will decline any
offers of help.

836
00:55:02.332 --> 00:55:04.401
If I survive this war...

837
00:55:04.701 --> 00:55:07.304
I will continue as I began...

838
00:55:09.072 --> 00:55:10.340
alone.

839
00:55:14.711 --> 00:55:17.847
(solemn music playing)

840
00:55:34.164 --> 00:55:35.865
(panting)

841
00:55:38.568 --> 00:55:41.338
- (dragon calls)
- (gasps)

842
00:55:41.404 --> 00:55:44.808
(tense. exciting music playing)

843
00:55:48.478 --> 00:55:50.647
(dragon calls)

844
00:55:57.787 --> 00:56:01.291
(music fades out)

845
00:56:01.358 --> 00:56:04.961
Mysaria: You have done what
no one else would dream of.

846
00:56:05.028 --> 00:56:07.897
and you have been rewarded.

847
00:56:07.964 --> 00:56:10.300
The gods favor you.

848
00:56:11.034 --> 00:56:14.070
They put the means to
victory in your hands.

849
00:56:14.137 --> 00:56:18.208
And yet. to claim
it. I must strike

850
00:56:18.274 --> 00:56:21.811
and in striking. I doom
thousands to their deaths.

851
00:56:21.878 --> 00:56:24.013
(dragons grumbling)

852
00:56:26.583 --> 00:56:29.886
I do not believe my father
would've wished this.

853
00:56:29.953 --> 00:56:32.122
He left you with no choice.

854
00:56:32.188 --> 00:56:35.759
Be strong. You
know you are just.

855
00:56:35.825 --> 00:56:37.627
You must not let the
Realm fall to those

856
00:56:37.694 --> 00:56:40.497
who care for power
more than peace.

857
00:56:40.864 --> 00:56:43.233
You must prevail.

858
00:56:46.102 --> 00:56:48.238
And who pays the price?

859
00:56:52.575 --> 00:56:55.745
(dragons grumbling. screeching)

860
00:57:01.351 --> 00:57:03.086
(bangs on door)

861
00:57:06.189 --> 00:57:07.357
Come.

862
00:57:07.424 --> 00:57:09.492
(door opens)

863
00:57:11.828 --> 00:57:13.997
Begging your pardon. Your Grace.

864
00:57:27.310 --> 00:57:29.446
I had to see you.

865
00:57:38.087 --> 00:57:39.856
- Who knows?
- None save my protector.

866
00:57:39.923 --> 00:57:42.358
He laid down his
sword at your gate.

867
00:57:45.094 --> 00:57:46.596
(sighs)

868
00:57:51.935 --> 00:57:56.339
I've been. I
think... mistaken.

869
00:57:58.274 --> 00:57:59.509
In what?

870
00:58:00.376 --> 00:58:03.480
I was raised to believe
there was an order to things.

871
00:58:03.546 --> 00:58:08.117
that there was security in
following the paths laid out for us.

872
00:58:08.885 --> 00:58:10.019
I resented you. I think.

873
00:58:10.086 --> 00:58:12.288
for... caring so
little for any of it.

874
00:58:12.355 --> 00:58:15.124
for knowing what you wanted.

875
00:58:15.558 --> 00:58:17.627
I did not know what I wanted.

876
00:58:18.061 --> 00:58:20.497
I knew only what
was expected of me.

877
00:58:23.500 --> 00:58:26.736
- Why have you come here?
- Because I lost my way.

878
00:58:26.803 --> 00:58:29.506
Or rather. it was taken from me.

879
00:58:29.873 --> 00:58:31.875
All those I put
my faith in. my...

880
00:58:31.941 --> 00:58:34.944
- m-my husband. my father. my lover. my son...
- Ooh.

881
00:58:35.011 --> 00:58:36.713
The incorruptible queen

882
00:58:36.779 --> 00:58:38.181
sullies herself with a lover.

883
00:58:38.248 --> 00:58:40.448
Do not judge me for what
you yourself have done.

884
00:58:40.950 --> 00:58:43.686
Your father died. I took
comfort with another.

885
00:58:44.187 --> 00:58:47.891
- I too have desires.
- Yes. but you alone made virtue your banner.

886
00:58:47.957 --> 00:58:51.094
And I clung to it...
in defiance of you.

887
00:58:51.160 --> 00:58:53.930
I think. who so disdained it.

888
00:59:04.707 --> 00:59:06.843
I have been alone. of late.

889
00:59:06.910 --> 00:59:09.112
I walked outside the
walls of the city

890
00:59:09.178 --> 00:59:11.314
and I felt a weight
lifted from me.

891
00:59:11.581 --> 00:59:14.317
- How lovely for you.
- I thought. for the first time.

892
00:59:14.384 --> 00:59:16.386
what I would choose...

893
00:59:16.853 --> 00:59:18.655
if not for the duty I
put before all else.

894
00:59:18.721 --> 00:59:22.559
(chuckles) Shall you cast
your son down and rule alone?

895
00:59:22.625 --> 00:59:25.328
No. I do not wish to
rule. I wish to live.

896
00:59:25.795 --> 00:59:29.365
To be free of all this
endless plotting and striving.

897
00:59:29.432 --> 00:59:31.668
The crown will pursue war
and victory at any cost.

898
00:59:31.734 --> 00:59:36.406
I... (sniffles)
But as for me...

899
00:59:36.472 --> 00:59:40.443
I would take my daughter and her
child and leave it all behind.

900
00:59:41.544 --> 00:59:45.381
(chuckles) It's too
late... Alicent.

901
00:59:46.449 --> 00:59:49.252
You said it yourself.
Blood has been shed.

902
00:59:49.319 --> 00:59:51.254
cities burned. armies march.

903
00:59:51.321 --> 00:59:53.256
and you wish to wash your hands

904
00:59:53.323 --> 00:59:54.924
of what you yourself
set in motion.

905
00:59:54.991 --> 00:59:56.492
Oh. the arrogance of blaming me.

906
00:59:56.559 --> 00:59:58.304
as if you would not have
been challenged regardless.

907
00:59:58.328 --> 01:00:00.339
Did not your hand bring
it forth like a midwife?

908
01:00:00.363 --> 01:00:03.066
I did only what I thought
your father wanted.

909
01:00:05.168 --> 01:00:06.903
Oh. go then.

910
01:00:07.971 --> 01:00:09.405
Leave us behind. as you say.

911
01:00:09.472 --> 01:00:11.040
(scoffs) Rhaenyra.

912
01:00:11.674 --> 01:00:14.344
- Wander in the wilderness.
- (Alicent sighs)

913
01:00:14.410 --> 01:00:16.579
What has it got to do with me?

914
01:00:20.617 --> 01:00:23.920
Did you come here thinking
you would be absolved?

915
01:00:29.626 --> 01:00:31.127
(sighs)

916
01:00:42.739 --> 01:00:45.541
He never stopped loving
your mother. you know?

917
01:00:46.109 --> 01:00:48.011
He was very fond of
me. and I of him.

918
01:00:48.077 --> 01:00:49.345
but...

919
01:00:50.113 --> 01:00:52.515
she was the vision
that sustained him

920
01:00:53.282 --> 01:00:54.417
even after she herself

921
01:00:54.484 --> 01:00:56.819
had slipped from
his grasp. it was

922
01:00:56.886 --> 01:00:58.688
his love for her that
kept him resolute

923
01:00:58.755 --> 01:01:00.456
in his choice of heir.

924
01:01:00.523 --> 01:01:03.159
And yet. you believe
he wavered at the end.

925
01:01:09.432 --> 01:01:11.567
Why have you come here?

926
01:01:12.135 --> 01:01:13.469
(sniffles)

927
01:01:14.037 --> 01:01:17.340
Aemond will soon fly to
join Cole in the Riverlands.

928
01:01:18.141 --> 01:01:19.542
(deep breath)

929
01:01:19.609 --> 01:01:21.010
When he's gone...

930
01:01:21.477 --> 01:01:23.613
Helaena as queen will be
the crown's authority.

931
01:01:23.680 --> 01:01:25.920
If you come then to King's
Landing. I will see to it

932
01:01:25.948 --> 01:01:27.650
that our guards throw
down their arms.

933
01:01:27.717 --> 01:01:30.920
we will open the gates.
we will shed no blood.

934
01:01:31.587 --> 01:01:34.424
- You will enter as a conqueror.
- (laughs)

935
01:01:35.491 --> 01:01:37.694
Already you have
the stronger hand.

936
01:01:38.661 --> 01:01:39.962
Once you take the throne...

937
01:01:40.029 --> 01:01:43.733
(deep breath) this
senseless war must end.

938
01:01:46.269 --> 01:01:47.770
(softly) Right.

939
01:01:51.908 --> 01:01:53.209
What of Aegon?

940
01:02:00.383 --> 01:02:03.786
He's broken beyond recognition.

941
01:02:05.088 --> 01:02:08.224
He lies in the dark.
in pain and terror.

942
01:02:08.624 --> 01:02:10.426
He has many faults. but...

943
01:02:11.294 --> 01:02:12.454
he still heeds his mother.

944
01:02:12.495 --> 01:02:13.830
I believe I can prevail upon him

945
01:02:13.896 --> 01:02:17.233
- to bend the knee. if indeed...
- No! Still...

946
01:02:17.300 --> 01:02:19.035
you defend him.

947
01:02:20.536 --> 01:02:23.906
Still you imagine you
can have all you want

948
01:02:23.973 --> 01:02:25.350
without paying too high a price.

949
01:02:25.374 --> 01:02:27.710
- a price I had no choice but to pay.
- What I want

950
01:02:27.777 --> 01:02:29.912
is to set things right.

951
01:02:31.781 --> 01:02:33.549
If I am to take the throne.

952
01:02:33.616 --> 01:02:36.953
I must put an end
to the opposition.

953
01:02:37.019 --> 01:02:38.354
I must take Aegon's head.

954
01:02:38.421 --> 01:02:40.389
And I have to do
it for all to see.

955
01:02:40.456 --> 01:02:42.158
You know this.

956
01:02:43.693 --> 01:02:46.729
However you may try to
evade it. you know this.

957
01:02:57.540 --> 01:02:58.808
Choose.

958
01:02:59.742 --> 01:03:01.844
(deep breath)

959
01:03:08.084 --> 01:03:10.953
Will you shrink from
what you set out to do?

960
01:03:11.020 --> 01:03:13.189
Or will you see it through...

961
01:03:14.357 --> 01:03:16.159
and make your sacrifice?

962
01:03:21.164 --> 01:03:23.266
A son for a son.

963
01:03:41.818 --> 01:03:43.319
(exhales)

964
01:03:46.322 --> 01:03:47.824
(sniffles)

965
01:03:55.164 --> 01:03:56.465
(sighs)

966
01:04:00.469 --> 01:04:02.572
(deep breath)

967
01:04:03.673 --> 01:04:06.008
(both crying softly)

968
01:04:16.319 --> 01:04:18.287
You are much changed.

969
01:04:18.721 --> 01:04:22.191
(sniffling) Let us be
done with this. please.

970
01:04:24.360 --> 01:04:26.929
And what do I do with you now?

971
01:04:28.564 --> 01:04:33.336
You let me go. to
do what I promised.

972
01:04:33.402 --> 01:04:35.738
And you fly to the Red
Keep in three days' time.

973
01:04:35.805 --> 01:04:37.874
and you take your throne.

974
01:04:37.940 --> 01:04:41.043
Or you take me for a liar.

975
01:04:41.110 --> 01:04:42.487
I have neither weapon nor armor.

976
01:04:42.511 --> 01:04:43.713
My life itself is forfeit.

977
01:04:43.779 --> 01:04:46.949
I... cast myself on
the mercy of a friend

978
01:04:47.016 --> 01:04:49.118
who once loved me.

979
01:04:50.820 --> 01:04:52.622
History will paint
you a villain.

980
01:04:56.859 --> 01:04:58.961
A cold queen...

981
01:05:01.364 --> 01:05:04.133
grasping for power.
and then defeated.

982
01:05:04.667 --> 01:05:06.869
Let them think what they must.

983
01:05:09.272 --> 01:05:11.407
I am at last myself...

984
01:05:12.141 --> 01:05:17.146
with no ambition greater than to walk
where I please and to breathe the open air.

985
01:05:19.548 --> 01:05:22.385
To die unremarked
and unnoticed...

986
01:05:23.920 --> 01:05:25.621
and be free.

987
01:05:29.158 --> 01:05:31.794
You speak as if from
a distant dream.

988
01:05:32.662 --> 01:05:34.163
Come with me.

989
01:05:37.967 --> 01:05:42.171
My part is here.
whether I will or no.

990
01:05:43.139 --> 01:05:45.942
It was decided for me long ago.

991
01:05:52.348 --> 01:05:54.283
(softly) Go.

992
01:05:58.854 --> 01:06:01.991
(melancholy music playing)

993
01:06:20.176 --> 01:06:22.144
(music intensifies)

994
01:06:52.308 --> 01:06:54.010
(panting)

995
01:06:54.643 --> 01:06:56.712
♪♪

996
01:07:01.117 --> 01:07:04.520
(tense. anticipatory
music playing)

997
01:07:18.300 --> 01:07:20.703
(roars)

998
01:07:28.711 --> 01:07:30.780
♪♪

999
01:07:50.533 --> 01:07:52.601
♪♪

1000
01:08:07.216 --> 01:08:09.285
♪♪

1001
01:08:27.436 --> 01:08:29.505
♪♪

1002
01:09:00.436 --> 01:09:02.505
♪♪

1003
01:09:10.346 --> 01:09:12.114
(panting)

1004
01:09:16.652 --> 01:09:18.821
(dragon grumbles)

1005
01:09:22.992 --> 01:09:24.293
(roars)

1006
01:09:25.094 --> 01:09:27.163
♪♪

1007
01:09:39.408 --> 01:09:41.977
(singers vocalizing)

1008
01:09:59.995 --> 01:10:02.097
(animals chattering)

1009
01:10:07.236 --> 01:10:09.038
♪♪

1010
01:10:09.104 --> 01:10:11.273
(vocalizing continues)

1011
01:10:32.261 --> 01:10:34.863
(music. vocalizing fades out)

1012
01:10:38.601 --> 01:10:41.737
(intense music playing)

1013
01:11:12.234 --> 01:11:14.303
♪♪

1014
01:11:31.186 --> 01:11:33.756
(singers vocalizing)

1015
01:11:45.301 --> 01:11:47.636
(music. vocalizing fades out)

1016
01:11:48.305 --> 01:12:48.853
